<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-14T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4001a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-14T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1315. Discreetly ascertain from <persName corresp="#p_MPN1">Milyukov</persName> if it would be acceptable if this
                                Government should send a commission of distinguished Americans to
                                consult with the Russian Government as to the best means of
                                cooperation and to convey a message of good will from the United
                                States. If such a commission would be acceptable also discreetly
                                ascertain whether it would be wise to have a prominent Hebrew a
                                member of the commission and whether the question as to this
                                Hebrew’s being orthodox or unorthodox is material. Answer as soon as
                                possible.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>